<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-4B086268-3AA3-43BA-AAB7-B73ECEDC28FA" version="3" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-4B086268-3AA3-43BA-AAB7-B73ECEDC28FA" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">SAM : The 'Synchronize certified time' procedure</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M153739-B56"><p class="- topic/p ">To synchronize the time on the SAM key, there are 2 possibilities: 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">A manual synchronization 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">An automatic synchronisation with every backup. 
</p></li></ol><p class="- topic/p "> The certified time needs to be update regularly other wise the SAM key will stop working. The interval at the moment is 2 months. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">At the end there are some guidelines for configuring CodeMeter WebAdmin. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Tools</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="M153739-B57" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/><note id="M153739-NOE58" type="note" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">if you are using a VPN connection, close it before you execute the procedure below, otherwise the time synchronization will fail. 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-394CAAAA-4A21-4841-9C9A-720468DBB6F5" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">A manual synchronization</title><table id="M153739-TB80" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="7*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="64*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="29*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Click on the WebAdmin button in CodeMeter Control Center: 
</p><fig outputclass="figure" id="M153739-F60" class="- topic/fig "><image href="IL059298-low.jpg" id="M153739-SH61" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="IL059298-low.jpg"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">A new tab will open in your browser and the CodeMeter WebAdmin window appears: 
</p><fig outputclass="figure" id="M153739-F62" class="- topic/fig "><image href="IL059299-low.jpg" id="M153739-SH63" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="IL059299-low.jpg"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">or
</p><fig id="GUID-071C9A66-4156-423C-9E3E-B621A77ADF27" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-96658027-5265-4019-A7FD-17AB11287540-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-96658027-5265-4019-A7FD-17AB11287540-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">In this window you see the System Time and the Certified Time. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">For this system the maximum difference between these two times is 60 days. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If the difference is larger, you will get a notification (a single beep or a message depending on the type of product) when you insert the SAM key. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">To update the time click on the “Update” button. You will get the window: 
</p><fig outputclass="figure" id="M153739-F64" class="- topic/fig "><image href="IL059300-low.jpg" id="M153739-SH65" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="IL059300-low.jpg"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">or Click on the button with the 2 arrows (at the right hand side of the screen).
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Click OK. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">You will get: 
</p><fig outputclass="figure" id="M153739-F66" class="- topic/fig "><image href="IL059301-low.jpg" id="M153739-SH67" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="IL059301-low.jpg"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Followed by: 
</p><fig outputclass="figure" id="M153739-F68" class="- topic/fig "><image href="IL059302-low.jpg" id="M153739-SH69" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="IL059302-low.jpg"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Now the system time and certified time are synchronized again. 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-3398B1EC-185C-4775-91BF-18DCF25EA7B2" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">An automatic synchronization with every backup.</title><table id="M153739-TB81" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="90*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">In CodeMeter WebAdmin &gt; Configuration &gt; Backup you can select to update the certified time before each backup. 
</p><fig outputclass="figure" id="M153739-F77" class="- topic/fig "><image href="IL074414-low.jpg" id="M153739-SH79" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="IL074414-low.jpg"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Updating the certified time can be combined with the backup. Default it is not done, but if you select the marked setting and leave the remaining backup settings at their default, the certified time is updated every day. 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-544B952C-4EEC-4449-B18F-C3B9B2F40660" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Notes regarding the configuration of CodeMeter WebAdmin</title><table id="M153739-TB86" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="90*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">WebAdmin uses the proxy settings of your web browser. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">You can change them via the Configuration &gt; Proxy page: 
</p></li></ul><fig outputclass="figure" id="M153739-F87" class="- topic/fig "><image href="IL059303-low.jpg" id="M153739-SH88" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="IL059303-low.jpg"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">If time synchronization fails due to missing or wrong proxy settings you will get an error message: 
</p><fig outputclass="figure" id="M153739-F89" class="- topic/fig "><image href="IL059987-low.jpg" id="M153739-SH90" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="IL059987-low.jpg"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-B8949918-A598-4816-BDAF-C06A30443D3A.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>SAM: Service Access Management</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>